HEADWORD: ack-ack
<hw>ack-ack</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[from <ets>AA</ets>, meaning
<ets>antiaircraft</ets> pronounced <ets>ack-ack</ets> by British
signalmen.]</ety> <fld>(Mil.)</fld> <def>Artillery designed to shoot
upward at airplanes; antiaircraft artillery.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> antiaircraft, antiaircraft gun, flak, pompom,
pom-pom, ack-ack gun</syn>⟦br⟧
